V = 4/3 × π × r³

Given radius (r) = 1.44 pm = 0.144 nm (convert pm to nm)

V = 4/3 × π × (0.144 nm)³ ≈ 30.35 cubic nanometers (or Å³)

Next, we'll calculate the edge length (a) of the FCC unit cell:

a = [(4 × V) / 3]^(1/3)
= [(4 × 30.35 cubic nanometers) / 3]^(1/3)
≈ 4.08 Å (angstroms)

So, the edge length of gold (Au) is approximately 4.08 Å.assistant

**Density of gold:**

The density of gold (ρ) can be calculated using the atomic mass (m), the Avogadro constant (NA), and the volume of the unit cell (V):

ρ = m × NA / V 

First, let's convert the atomic mass from amu to g/mol:
m = 197 amu × (1 g/mol) / 6.022 × 10²³ amu 
≈ 196.9665 g/mol 

Now, plug in the values:
ρ = 196.9665 g/mol × 6.022 × 10²³ mol⁻¹ / 68.36 Å³ 
≈ 19.3 g/cm³
